  "name": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending — Credibility Assessment Package",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The governing requirement specifies that verification of construct stiffness and yield-force predictions shall be performed via a controlled experiment in which boundary conditions, loading rates, and environmental parameters are fully prescribed and independently replicated. The supporting validation activity — a multi-site observational data-collection exercise drawing on retrospectively assembled bench-test records from two independent laboratories — is described at length in Section 4 of the technical report and is cited throughout this package as the primary evidence base. Both activities involve physical hardware and force-displacement instrumentation, and the observational study provides rich multi-laboratory coverage that substantially strengthens confidence in the predictions. The structured activity record reflects the actual data-collection protocol employed.",
